These are the links to download and install the basic softwares:

1. Install Anaconda ---> https://docs.anaconda.com/free/anaconda/install/linux/
2. Install Fermi-Conda ---> https://github.com/fermi-lat/Fermitools-conda/wiki/Installation-Instructions
3. SciServer HEASARC User Guide ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/sciserver/
4. Install CFITSIO ---> https://www.gnu.org/software/gnuastro/manual/html_node/CFITSIO.html
5. Install Jupyter Notebook & Lab ---> https://jupyter.org/install
OR
https://towardsdatascience.com/how-to-set-up-anaconda-and-jupyter-notebook-the-right-way-de3b7623ea4a
6. HEASOFT Tools page ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/lheasoft/
7. Download HEASOFT software ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/lheasoft/download.html
8. Install Heasoft ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/lheasoft/ubuntu.html
OR
https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/lheasoft/install.html
9. FermiPY Installation ---> https://fermipy.readthedocs.io/en/latest/install.html
10. Install Geos ---> https://libgeos.org/usage/download/
11. Install geos with basemap ---> https://matplotlib.org/basemap/users/installing.html#installation
or
https://github.com/matplotlib/basemap/releases/
12. GBM Software Tools ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/gbm/
13. Install gspec ---> https://indico.cern.ch/event/783425/contributions/3361524/attachments/1814497/2965032/GSPEC.pdf
14. Install GBM ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/gbm/gbm_data_tools/gdt-docs/install.html
15. Install Enrico ---> https://enrico.readthedocs.io/en/latest/setup.html


These are the links to download the data for the Fermi Telescope data analysis:

1. Fermi Data Access ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/access/
2. Source Search Simbad ---> http://simbad.cds.unistra.fr/simbad/sim-fbasic
3. HEASARC Source to Download LAT/GBM files ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/FTP/fermi/data/
4. GBM FILES ARCHIVE ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/FTP/fermi/data/gbm/triggers/
5. Fermi Catalog Source to Download tar files of GBM ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/db-perl/W3Browse/w3table.pl?tablehead=name%3Dfermigbrst&Action=More+Options
or
https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/db-perl/W3Browse/w3table.pl?tablehead=name%3Dfermigbrst&Action=More+Options
or
https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/W3Browse/fermi/fermigbrst.html


Additional Information
1. All about GBM Satellite ---> https://gammaray.nsstc.nasa.gov/gbm/publications/
2. Formula for models ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/source_models.html#Gaussian
3. Formula for GBM models ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/gbm/gbm_data_tools/gdt-docs/api/api-spectra.html
4. GBM Documentation ---> https://gammaray.nsstc.nasa.gov/gbm/publications/proposal/GBM-proposal.pdf
5. BAT ---> https://swift.gsfc.nasa.gov/analysis/bat_swguide_v6_3.pdf


Following are the tutorials used for the thorough understanding of data analysis for the Fermi LAT and GBM.

1. Time Converter from MET to MJD ---> https://heasarc.gsfc.nasa.gov/cgi-bin/Tools/xTime/xTime.pl

Fermi LAT Analysis for GRBs ===>
1. https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/extract_latdata.html
2. https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/cgi-bin/ssc/LAT/LATDataQuery.cgi
3. https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/explore_latdata_burst.html
4. https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/lat_grb_analysis.html
5. Fermi LAT Gamma-Ray Burst Analysis ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/lat_grb_analysis.html
6. Fermi GTBurst ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/gtburst.html

Fermi LAT Analysis for AGNs ===>
1. Fermi Unbinned Likelihood Tutorial ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/likelihood_tutorial.html
2. Fermi Binned Likelihood Tutorial ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/binned_likelihood_tutorial.html
3. Fermi User Contributed Models ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/user/
4. Fermi LAT Background Models ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/access/lat/BackgroundModels.html
5. Fermi Likelihood Analysis with Python ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/analysis/scitools/python_tutorial.html
or 
(Complete) https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/data/p7rep/analysis/scitools/python_tutorial.html
or
https://notebooks.githubusercontent.com/view/ipynb?azure_maps_enabled=true&browser=chrome&color_mode=auto&commit=e502da5e45480b3538bb3a1ebcd29bd75d6e3ff1&device=unknown&enc_&logged_in=false&nwo=fermi-lat%2FAnalysisThreads&path=SourceAnalysis%2F3.PythonLikelihood%2Fpython_tutorial.ipynb&platform=android&repository_id=191190607&repository_type=Repository&version=103
6. Mistakes in Likelihood Analysis ---> https://github.com/fermi-lat/Likelihood/issues/110
or
https://github.com/fermi-lat/Likelihood/issues/107
7. Fermi LAT GRBs ---> https://fermi.gsfc.nasa.gov/ssc/observations/types/grbs/lat_grbs/

